The Duke of Sussex, 37, has said that he will not return for the memorial - and has cited security concerns. Commenting on the announcement that King Felipe and Queen Letizia of Spain will attend the service, Daily Mail diary editor Richard Eden appeared to mock Harry's decision not to return to "dangerous" London. He said: "This is lovely news that the King and Queen of Spain are travelling to Prince Philip's memorial service in 'dangerous' London." A legal representative for the Duke previously said Harry wants to bring his children to the UK - but they are "unable to return to his home" because it is too dangerous. FOLLOW BELOW FOR LIVE UPDATES...